| Feature          | Promise     | async/await     | Observable (RxJS)       |
| ---------------- | ----------- | --------------- | ----------------------- |
| Multiple values? | âŒ No        | âŒ No            | âœ… Yes (streams)         |
| Cancellation?    | âŒ No        | âŒ No            | âœ… Yes (`unsubscribe()`) |
| Built-in in JS?  | âœ… Yes       | âœ… Yes           | âŒ No (external lib)     |
| Syntax Style     | `.then()`   | `await`         | `.subscribe()`          |
| Usage            | All JS apps | Modern JS/React | Angular, Reactive Apps  |


ðŸš€ When to Use What?

âœ… Promise: One-time async operation (e.g., fetch data).

âœ… async/await: Clean syntax for working with promises.

âœ… Observable: Real-time data, streams, WebSockets, form control events, etc. (especially in Angular).

const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  setTimeout(() => resolve("Done"), 1000);
});

promise.then(data => console.log(data)).catch(err => console.error(err));



async function getData() {
  try {
    const result = await fetch("https://api.example.com/data");
    const data = await result.json();
    console.log(data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
  }
}


import { Observable } from 'rxjs';

const obs = new Observable(subscriber => {
  subscriber.next("A");
  setTimeout(() => subscriber.next("B"), 1000);
  setTimeout(() => subscriber.complete(), 2000);
});

obs.subscribe({
  next: val => console.log(val),
  complete: () => console.log("Done"),
});
